  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-09-23",
    "date": "2021-11-05T14:10:21Z",
    "text": "Transparency in COVID-19 Expenditures Act\n\nThis bill requires the Government Accountability Office (GAO) to audit certain funding that was provided to address COVID-19.\n\nSpecifically, the GAO must audit and report on the use of funding provided by\n\n the Coronavirus Preparedness and Response Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2020; the Families First Coronavirus Response Act; the Coronavirus Aid, Relief, and Economic Security Act (CARES Act); the Paycheck Protection Program and Health Care Enhancement Act; Divisions M and N of the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2021; and the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021."
  },
